Oh wow, okay. I never turn down a request if it’ll help somebody! I just don’t have any serious knowledge on anorexia. (I mean with depression fics I can use my own experience)

summary: Okay but listen. I know this probably won't make sense, but what if A4 ends with Tony walking onto a spankin' new helicarrier,...
body: Okay but listen. I know this probably won’t make sense, but what if A4 ends with Tony walking onto a spankin’ new helicarrier, he’s bruised and broken but he has a glint of determination in his eyes y'know. It’s quiet and he lifts one arm and a bunch of holograms spring up and start moving across his field of vision and he’s like “See? Much better. Nicky needed to get with the program.” and then an amused Maria Hill (loml fight me) clears her throat and she’s like “Director Stark? Awaiting orders, sir.” and it ends with a close up of Tony doing that little smirk? You know the one. And then badass end credit scene.

summary: hard to see beyond what's in sight
title: hard to see beyond what's in sight
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2EiMqVe

by paperclipsentimental

Phil smiles, slow and easy and; “Here’s what we’re going to do,” he asserts. “You’re just going to lie there and I’m going to make you come, maybe with my fingers but maybe with my mouth, and maybe I’ll teach you how to please Nat, too.”

Clint gives a full body tremble and his lashes flutter, so Nat runs her fingers through his hair just because he looks so pretty she can’t help it.

“Does that sound good to you, lovely?” she murmurs in his ear and he nods instantly.

“Yes,” he says.

Or, Clint, Phil and Natasha. Together.
